## User Experience Flow

1) User visits Billing area (Billing / Subscription Page)
- Sees current plan, next billing date, next invoice amount, and usage meters.
- Can update payment method; add a new card via Stripe Elements; set as default.

2) User initiates a Checkout for a subscription or add-on (Checkout / Payment Page)
- Selects plan and any add-ons; reviews order summary; enters coupon if available; sees prorated amount if upgrading mid-cycle.
- Proceeds to payment; Stripe Elements collect card details; authentication handled as required (SCA/3DS).
- On success: user is redirected to Transaction History with a success receipt; local subscription updated; next invoice generated.

3) User reviews Transactions / Order History
- Filters by date range, status (paid, pending, failed), plan, or add-ons.
- Clicks an invoice to view details; downloads PDF or Stripe-hosted receipt.

4) Admin workflow (Admin UI)
- Admin views all invoices, issues refunds, adjusts line items, or changes plans with proration details.
- Admin can view audit trails and export decision logs for contracts/records.

5) Webhook-driven events
- Payment succeeds: local invoice marked paid; user receives receipt.
- Payment fails: user notified; potential retry logic displayed.
- Subscription changes: plan upgrades/downgrades applied with prorated charges; UI reflects new plan and upcoming invoice.

